Cobb's coach/Cobb coach
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:generic term for specific type of coach, thorough-braced, rather than sprung, popular in NZ and Aust. in the 19th and early 20th centuries.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:Cobb & Co
